GTE Spacenet Corp. said it signed a $20 million contract to provide satellite transponder service to the Cable News Network unit of Turner Broadcasting Systems Inc. 

GTE Spacenet is a unit of GTE Corp., a telecommunications, lighting and precision materials company in Stamford, Conn. 

CO LPL+ ETR .START 

Louisiana Power & Light Co., a unit of Entergy Corp., said it will redeem in entirety on Oct. 27, five series of first mortgage bonds at 100% of the principal plus interest. 

The utility said it will use the about $353.6 million in cash proceeds from the planned sale and lease-back of a portion of its Waterford 3 nuclear plant in Taft, La., to finance the redemption. 

The first mortgage bonds to be redeemed by Louisiana Power & Light are $35 million of a 15 1/4% series due Dec. 1, 2014; $100 million of a 16% series due Aug. 1, 1994; $55 million of a 14 3/4% series due Nov. 1, 2014; $100 million of a 13 1/4% series due March 1, 2013 and $50 million of 13% first mortgage bonds due Sept. 1, 2013.
Entergy is a utility holding company. 

